I'm very very proud to be his teacher in school. I visited him for my muscle stretch in the back. His touch is MIDAS touch. I was completely normal in two weeks. My husband was knocked down by a motorcyclist and had neck femur fracture in the left leg. Thursday my husband fell, Friday Dr Hitesh operated on him and Saturday he was able to walk with Walker. Hats off to him.
Dear Hitesh you have once again proved HKS means *Hitesh Kubadia Special* touch HEALS. God bless you always and may you succeed in every operation you perform. Love you dear. Lots of love and blessings kulkarniteacher.

Very smart, smiling, jolly energetic doctor. does not get tired to answer patient's 100 querries. Before operaion,his sweet polite words removes patient's mental tension and gets prepared, ready mentally & physically for the operation.  Opration is carried out with minimum muscles cutting so that recovery and healing is faster. During opertation his smiling face gives confidence & patience to patient to sustain major operation. Even after operation he was loving & care takiing and gave visits to patient in the hospital to ensure that patient is in comfortable condition with bearable pains and all other things going smoothly. At all this time he was so friendly that we felt that he is our close relative or a member of our family. We wish him great success & happy life in future.
